data.text:
The hilarious Margaret Cho is coming to Capitol Theatre on Thursday, May 2nd. We've got your chance to win a pair of tickets to her show.

Though many know the name from her numerous appearances on comedy specials, tv shows, and so much more, newer audiences may recognize her from The Flight Attendant and on Hacks, both shows on MAX.

Margaret Cho currently has two Netflix is a Joke comedy specials as well.

She's has been listed as one of the best stand-up comics of all time according to Rolling Stone magazine, one of the top 9 female comedians of all time according to Vogue magazine and one of the 50 people who have changed American comedy from CNN.

People in the Yakima Valley were excited when we first broke news that Margaret Cho was going to come to Yakima a little while back and the time is almost here.

She's only in town one day so don't miss out! Check out Capitol Theatre's website to buy your tickets now.

Warning: language

Margaret Cho

Capitol Theatre in Yakima

Thursday, May 2, 2024

Doors open at 6:30. Show starts at 7:30

This show contains mature content.

LOOK: 50 famous memes and what they mean

With the infinite number of memes scattered across the internet, it's hard to keep track. Just when you've grasped the meaning of one hilarious meme, it has already become old news and replaced by something equally as enigmatic. Online forums like Tumblr, Twitter, 4chan, and Reddit are responsible for a majority of meme infections, and with the constant posting and sharing, finding the source of an original meme is easier said than done. Stacker hunted through internet resources, pop culture publications, and databases like Know Your Meme to find 50 different memes and what they mean. While the almost self-replicating nature of these vague symbols can get exhausting, memes in their essence can also bring people closer together—as long as they have internet access.
